1
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:37,133
<i>- Jessica!
- I'm done!</i>

2
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> I just want to go home!</i>

3
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,100
<i> Coleen, stop!</i>

4
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:41,067
<i>- Jessica, please!
- Let me go!</i>

5
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,800
<i>- Jessica!
- Let me go!</i>

6
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,267
<i> Jessica!</i>

7
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,967
<i> Jessica!</i>

8
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:50,733
<i> Jessica!</i>

9
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:51,567
<i> What did you do?</i>

10
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:52,200
<i> Nothing!</i>

11
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,233
<i> What happened?</i>

12
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:55,667
<i> I didn't do anything!</i>

13
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:56,867
<i> Mommy's here.</i>

14
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,300
<i>We'll take care
of your daughter.</i>

15
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:00,333
<i> I didn't mean it.</i>

16
00:01:00,467 --> 00:01:03,167
<i>Not a single one of them
even replied.</i>

17
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:05,233
<i> Is Jessica with them?</i>

18
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:06,433
<i> Hello, Mom?</i>

19
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,900
<i>Why aren't you replying
to my text messages?</i>

20
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:10,633
<i> Jessica.</i>

21
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:12,833
<i>Something bad's happening
to Jessica.</i>

22
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:14,033
<i> Friend.</i>

23
00:01:14,167 --> 00:01:16,267
<i> Friend, calm down.</i>

24
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,333
<i> Jessica is in good hands.</i>

25
00:01:18,467 --> 00:01:19,833
<i> Rhythm check.</i>

26
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:20,933
<i> Charge to 350.</i>

27
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:25,200
<i> Clear.</i>

28
00:01:29,767 --> 00:01:30,700
<i> Continue CPR.</i>

29
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:37,867
Hush now.

30
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,200
Something bad is happening
to her.

31
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:40,167
That's enough.

32
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:42,233
We must know what's happening
to her.

33
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:45,200
Please stop. Nothing bad
will happen to Jessica.

34
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:46,300
Nothing.

35
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:47,867
I feel it.

36
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,300
I feel it, Alice.

37
00:01:50,233 --> 00:01:51,933
Hush now.

38
00:01:52,067 --> 00:01:53,967
Nurse Glo.

39
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,700
Nurse Glo, how's my daughter?

40
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:57,633
Did something wrong happen
to her?

41
00:01:57,767 --> 00:02:00,267
She was in asystole
for a few minutes.

42
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:03,867
She's got a pulse again.

43
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,900
We revived her.

44
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:08,267
The operation is still ongoing.

45
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,967
What's her status now?

46
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,400
Hazel, you know we can't
tell you anything

47
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:14,600
while the procedure is ongoing.

48
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:16,733
Please.

49
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,300
From a mother to another mother.

50
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,167
I'm begging you.

51
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,200
Please.

52
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:28,267
I need to know...

53
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,533
no matter how grave it is.

54
00:02:33,033 --> 00:02:34,867
What's going on
with my daughter?

55
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,200
I'm begging you.

56
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,067
Please.

57
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,100
This could get me in trouble,

58
00:02:41,233 --> 00:02:46,733
but if I were in your position,
I would also like to know.

59
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,800
Your daughter had a severe
head trauma.

60
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:51,633
She lost a lot of blood.

61
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:55,833
Dr. Restar's doing everything
to stabilize her.

62
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:58,000
So far, she's making progress.

63
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:01,367
Thank you.

64
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:04,900
Thank you.

65
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:05,933
Thank you so much.

66
00:03:06,067 --> 00:03:08,400
But she's still
in a critical condition, Hazel.

67
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:11,100
So, we still need
to fervently pray.

68
00:03:12,467 --> 00:03:13,733
Excuse me.

69
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:19,067
Friend, sit down for now.

70
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,533
Try to calm yourself. Come on.

71
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,367
I'll get you some water.

72
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,100
Stay here.

73
00:03:25,233 --> 00:03:26,033
Okay?

74
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:29,400
Lord...

75
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:31,833
Lord, please.

76
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:35,267
Save Jessica.

77
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:42,167
Please take care of her.

78
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:58,100
Friend.

79
00:03:58,233 --> 00:03:59,800
Here. Drink some water.

80
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:36,233
Have some coffee.

81
00:04:36,367 --> 00:04:37,700
Come on.

82
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:38,833
You need this.

83
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:22,267
I'll stay here.

84
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,233
I'll keep you updated.

85
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:25,967
No, Joel.

86
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:29,667
We'll stay together.

87
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:33,333
And you, Jeffrey and Coleen,
go and see our parents.

88
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:34,467
They might probably be awake
by now.

89
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:37,567
They might find it strange
that we're not there.

90
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:40,500
We'll follow
once we get an update here.

91
00:05:43,133 --> 00:05:43,933
We'll go ahead.

92
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:48,367
Okay.

93
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,100
Doctor.

94
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:56,100
Doctor, how was it?

95
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:02,100
We were able to revive her
and save her.

96
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:08,167
But we still have to put her
in the ICU.

97
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:23,333
Thank you.

98
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:24,800
Thank you.

99
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,033
Thank you.

100
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:27,033
Thank you, Lord.

101
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:34,767
Thank you.

102
00:06:45,367 --> 00:06:47,033
How's Jessica?

103
00:06:47,167 --> 00:06:48,167
Is there any news?

104
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:50,733
Her operation is still ongoing.

105
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,233
It's taking so long.

106
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,533
I hope my goddaughter makes it.

107
00:06:58,667 --> 00:07:00,100
So it'll be over.

108
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,033
What exactly will be over?

109
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,100
We hope...

110
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,200
dad's suffering will be over.

111
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,533
We hope he recovers completely.

112
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:17,700
Yes, son.

113
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:19,633
Soon.

114
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:22,233
Your dad is getting stronger.

115
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:26,000
What time is it?

116
00:07:29,733 --> 00:07:31,933
I think I slept
a little too long.

117
00:07:36,367 --> 00:07:37,500
Coleen?

118
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:40,467
Why do you look like that, dear?

119
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,700
What happened?

120
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:47,700
Manuel!

121
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:49,633
Welcome back.

122
00:07:49,767 --> 00:07:51,233
How are you feeling?

123
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:53,567
Jeff.

124
00:07:57,467 --> 00:07:58,267
Coleen.

125
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:04,800
Where's Andeng?

126
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,000
<i> Andrea.</i>

127
00:08:26,767 --> 00:08:27,833
Dad.

128
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,733
Andeng.

129
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:38,933
Let's leave them alone for now.

130
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:43,067
Coleen, let's go.

131
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:28,100
Mrs. Cruz, your daughter
sustained severe

132
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:30,200
craniofacial trauma.

133
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:36,267
Multiple facial skull fractures
due to the impact of her fall.

134
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:39,500
She survived the surgery.

135
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:41,133
The bleeding was controlled.

136
00:09:42,167 --> 00:09:44,167
But her condition
remains critical.

137
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:47,267
As you already know,

138
00:09:47,967 --> 00:09:51,200
head trauma poses the danger
of brain swelling,

139
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,467
or the accumulation of fluid
in the brain.

140
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:59,167
This could lead to increased
intracranial pressure,

141
00:09:59,767 --> 00:10:01,433
which could be fatal.

142
00:10:17,167 --> 00:10:18,167
Jessica...

143
00:10:20,167 --> 00:10:21,400
please fight.

144
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:26,633
Dear, get better.

145
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:29,467
Wake up.

146
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,900
Hang in there.

147
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:41,367
I won't let this slide.

148
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:47,000
I won't let them get away
with what they did to you.

149
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:49,167
<i> So, wake up.</i>

150
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:53,700
I want you to see
what I'll do to them.

151
00:11:06,467 --> 00:11:11,500
You're still wearing
the bracelet Jeff gave you.

152
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:21,167
Yes, I only removed this
when I had my surgery.

153
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:28,267
But when I woke up at
Hazel's house in the province,

154
00:11:30,367 --> 00:11:32,100
I saw that I was wearing it
again.

155
00:11:35,733 --> 00:11:38,200
I promised your older brother
I wouldn't remove it.

156
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:47,100
I also took care of your gift.

157
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:52,300
<i> That's you, Dad.</i>

158
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:54,067
<i> This is me.</i>

159
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:58,600
<i> This is mom, holding Coleen.</i>

160
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:00,900
<i> And Jeffrey.</i>

161
00:12:01,033 --> 00:12:05,267
<i>Look at it whenever you miss us.</i>

162
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,800
<i> Thank you, dear.</i>

163
00:12:06,933 --> 00:12:09,400
<i> And always bring your inhaler.</i>

164
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:11,600
<i>Get some rest if you're
having an asthma attack.</i>

165
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:13,500
<i>So that your heart problem
doesn't get worse.</i>

166
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:14,733
<i> Okay?</i>

167
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,233
I looked at it every day.

168
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,867
Because I missed you every day.

169
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:33,033
But Hazel saw it and burned it.

170
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,667
<i> Why did you burn it?</i>

171
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,067
<i>This is all I have left
to remember them by.</i>

172
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,733
<i>The nerve of you to keep
your trash here.</i>

173
00:12:40,867 --> 00:12:44,133
<i>Hazel, this is the only memory
I have left of them!</i>

174
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:45,800
<i> Good.</i>

175
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:48,267
<i>There's nothing else left for me
to burn.</i>

176
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:52,600
It's okay, Dad.

177
00:13:01,667 --> 00:13:02,833
Here.

178
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,833
I kept this for a long time,
Dad.

179
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:19,033
I always looked at this
whenever I missed you.

180
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,300
But I stopped when...

181
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,567
When I abandoned you.

182
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:36,767
Dear...

183
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,967
Dear, please forgive me.

184
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:43,867
I hope someday
you can forgive me

185
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,467
for everything I've done
to our family.

186
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:50,667
Andeng, my daughter...

187
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,733
I hope you can all forgive me.

188
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,133
Dad, I've already forgiven you.

189
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:10,467
But please forgive me, too,
because...

190
00:14:14,267 --> 00:14:15,700
it didn't happen right away.

191
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:21,200
I chose to stay angry
instead of forgiving you.

192
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:25,100
I'm sorry, Dad.

193
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:26,233
It's just...

194
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:30,700
I was so hurt.

195
00:14:34,067 --> 00:14:35,800
Dad, I love you so much, but...

196
00:14:37,567 --> 00:14:42,600
I didn't know how to understand
or accept...

197
00:14:42,733 --> 00:14:44,333
that the very person
I held onto...

198
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:45,533
was the one who left me.

199
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,667
I'm sorry, Dad,
for being disrespectful,

200
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,000
for being stubborn,

201
00:14:52,133 --> 00:14:54,667
even when you kept asking
for forgiveness.

202
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,133
I even disrespected mom, too.

203
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:03,467
I'm sorry.

204
00:15:06,633 --> 00:15:09,000
I'm sorry for letting
my heart grow hard.

205
00:15:09,767 --> 00:15:11,500
No.

206
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:16,067
Andeng, sweetie,
you don't need to say sorry.

207
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:19,500
I understand why your anger
ran so deep.

208
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:22,600
But don't worry.

209
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,067
I'll make it up to you.

210
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:28,433
I'll fix everything
I've done wrong.

211
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,900
Thank you, Dad.

212
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,900
Thank you for coming back to us.

213
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:48,167
Please don't ever leave us
again, okay?

214
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:51,000
- I won't, my dear.
- Promise, Dad?

215
00:15:51,133 --> 00:15:52,467
Never again.
I will never leave you.

216
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:57,333
I love you so, so much, Andeng.

217
00:16:00,133 --> 00:16:02,500
- I love you so, Andeng.
- I love you too, Dad.

218
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,767
I love you too, Dad.

219
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,467
I love you so, so much.

220
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,333
At last, the wound Andeng's been
carrying for so long

221
00:16:24,467 --> 00:16:26,900
is finally starting to heal.

222
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:28,267
Yeah.

223
00:16:29,433 --> 00:16:30,667
You're right.

224
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:42,567
Where's Jessica?

225
00:16:44,367 --> 00:16:45,533
I haven't seen her yet.

226
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,433
Are you hiding something
from me?

227
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:01,167
I've been watching you
since earlier.

228
00:17:04,167 --> 00:17:05,933
You two have been whispering
at each other.

229
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,467
What's going on?

230
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:10,000
Is there a problem?

231
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:14,467
Jeffrey!

232
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:16,433
Coleen!

233
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:19,200
Paz.

234
00:17:21,967 --> 00:17:22,700
Abel.

235
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:25,633
Joel.

236
00:17:27,533 --> 00:17:28,533
Coleen.

237
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:31,700
Something happened, Mom.

238
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:32,700
But everything's okay now.

239
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:35,133
Coleen, it's okay now.

240
00:17:37,467 --> 00:17:38,933
Right, Joel?

241
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:40,967
<i> What?</i>

242
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:41,733
Yes.

243
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:42,833
Everything's okay.

244
00:17:42,967 --> 00:17:45,033
What do you want to tell me?

245
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:54,600
You know, I've waited for
this moment for so long.

246
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:00,700
I thought I'd never get
to hold you again.

247
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,767
Me too, Dad.

248
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:06,833
You know what?

249
00:18:08,867 --> 00:18:11,100
I missed calling you "Andeng."

250
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:18,467
I missed it, too, Dad.

251
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:25,800
Did you know, Dad?

252
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:33,133
Mom and Jeff still call me
"Andeng."

253
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:35,533
Even Auntie Paz
and Uncle Abel do.

254
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:40,300
But it's different when
it's you who says it.

255
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:48,600
Dad...

256
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,800
Can we make this moment real?

257
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,633
Let's take a family picture...

258
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:05,200
as one whole family.

259
00:19:08,867 --> 00:19:09,867
Yes, my dear.

260
00:19:12,333 --> 00:19:14,933
Let's make our family real.

261
00:19:16,467 --> 00:19:19,167
We'll rebuild what we lost.

262
00:19:23,167 --> 00:19:31,667
Actually, I'm planning
to annul my marriage with Hazel.

263
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:34,967
Then, I'll court your mom again.

264
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:40,433
And when she says yes,
I'll marry her.

265
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:44,067
But only if it's okay
with you and your siblings.

266
00:19:46,033 --> 00:19:47,133
Wait, Dad.

267
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:53,433
Are you asking for permission,
or just telling me your plan?

268
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:56,433
Both.

269
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:58,967
Well, of course it's okay!

270
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,767
I'd love that, Dad.

271
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,567
I'm sure, Dad.

272
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,633
Jeff's okay with it, too.

273
00:20:14,033 --> 00:20:15,033
Andeng, sweetheart.

274
00:20:15,433 --> 00:20:19,400
There's one more thing
I want to ask.

275
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,333
If it's all right...

276
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:26,567
I hope you can also welcome
Jessica as part of our family.

277
00:20:28,367 --> 00:20:30,667
If possible, I'd like her
to be the youngest,

278
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:33,067
the baby of our family.

279
00:20:44,633 --> 00:20:45,867
What?

280
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,767
What are you not telling me?

281
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:51,733
Are you all waiting for me
to get angry?

282
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:52,600
Is that it? No.

283
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:54,300
Mom, please calm down.

284
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,400
We were going to tell you,
I promise, but...

285
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,000
please, don't tell dad yet,
okay?

286
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:03,467
Why?

287
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,367
What is it? Tell me right now!

288
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:09,867
Felma...

289
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,200
You monster!

290
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:13,600
So you've been here all along!

291
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:15,933
What are you doing here?

292
00:21:16,067 --> 00:21:18,233
You came to see Manuel?

293
00:21:18,367 --> 00:21:20,667
Where did you get that criminal
behavior of yours?

294
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:23,733
Mom!

295
00:21:23,867 --> 00:21:24,600
Mom, please stop!

296
00:21:30,467 --> 00:21:32,433
You're still defending
your daughter

297
00:21:32,567 --> 00:21:34,133
after what she did to mine?

298
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,033
What did she do?

299
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:37,233
You don't know?

300
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,733
These people kept it from you?

301
00:21:43,167 --> 00:21:47,733
My daughter is fighting
for her life in the ICU!

302
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:52,900
Jessica is in the ICU
because of that girl!

303
00:21:53,033 --> 00:21:54,967
- What?
- Because of Coleen!

304
00:21:58,433 --> 00:21:59,433
Coleen, admit it.

305
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:02,267
Admit it!

306
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:06,267
Admit that you pushed Jessica,

307
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,967
and that's why she got hit
by a car!

308
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:12,467
What?

309
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,567
Dear.

310
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,667
Dear.

311
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,167
What happened?

312
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:18,700
What happened?

313
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:20,100
Tell me!

314
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:21,667
What happened?

315
00:22:36,567 --> 00:22:39,367
If anything happens to Jessica,
you'll pay for it!

316
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:40,400
Stop it! Please stop!

317
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:43,167
Try to hurt my child
and see what happens!

318
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:45,200
- Try it!
- You'd still defend

319
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:46,733
your criminal daughter?

320
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:48,367
I was there!

321
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:49,367
Hey, Hazel!

322
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:51,233
Stop lying!

323
00:22:51,367 --> 00:22:53,700
We saw you hitting Coleen.

324
00:22:53,833 --> 00:22:55,433
That's why Andeng rushed over!

325
00:22:55,567 --> 00:22:57,333
That's why everything exploded!

326
00:22:57,467 --> 00:22:58,200
You weren't there!

327
00:22:58,333 --> 00:22:59,233
None of us were!

328
00:22:59,367 --> 00:23:00,567
Don't you dare lie!

329
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,633
What do you take my child for?

330
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:03,867
Stupid?

331
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,233
You think she'd throw herself
in front of a car?

332
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:09,033
Coleen, admit it!

333
00:23:09,167 --> 00:23:11,133
You pushed my daughter!

334
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:12,333
You pushed her!

335
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:15,800
Admit it!

336
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:17,700
Admit!

337
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:18,400
Stop!

338
00:23:18,533 --> 00:23:19,267
What's with you?

339
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:24,400
How did this happen?

340
00:23:24,567 --> 00:23:29,100
Jessica's been in an accident,
and no one told me?

341
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:30,300
Why?

342
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:31,233
Why didn't anyone say anything?

343
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:32,200
Felma, sorry.

344
00:23:32,333 --> 00:23:33,133
Sorry!

345
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:37,000
What?

346
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:38,200
Why didn't you know?

347
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:43,133
Even Manuel doesn't know
what happened to our daughter?

348
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:47,767
You people are monsters!

349
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:48,733
All of you!

350
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:50,533
Manuel!

351
00:23:50,667 --> 00:23:52,167
Stop it, Hazel!

352
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:53,933
Move!

353
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:55,367
What did you do to Jessica?

354
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:56,933
Did you hurt her again?

355
00:23:57,067 --> 00:23:59,033
Coleen, did!

356
00:23:59,167 --> 00:24:04,100
She's the reason our daughter's
fighting for her life!

357
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:05,267
They're evil.

358
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:07,367
They kept it from you!

359
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:10,300
Hazel, may I see our daughter?

360
00:24:12,733 --> 00:24:15,133
Mom, you shouldn't have left dad
with Hazel.

361
00:24:16,533 --> 00:24:18,033
What was the point
of bringing him home

362
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:19,433
if you were just going
to send him back?

363
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:23,600
Do you really think
she'd take your dad away?

364
00:24:23,733 --> 00:24:25,900
Jessica, sweetheart.

365
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:27,500
Your dad and I are both here.

366
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:32,833
We're fighting with you, okay?

367
00:24:32,967 --> 00:24:34,033
Don't give up, sweetheart.

368
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:36,867
I'm just right here.

369
00:24:38,467 --> 00:24:39,433
You're not alone.

370
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:41,500
Your fight is our fight, too.

371
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:47,767
Manuel, did you see that?

372
00:24:49,367 --> 00:24:51,700
I love you so much.

373
00:24:51,833 --> 00:24:53,000
We're here, dear.

374
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,200
We're here. We'll wait for you.
